   FCC Statements, Testimony & Other Material

     * Statement of Chairman Powell Before the Subcommittee on
       Telecommunications and the Internet of the House Committee on
       Energy and Commerce On the NEXTWAVE Settlement Legislation,
       December 11, 2001.
     * Statement of John Rogovin, Deputy General Counsel, Before the
       Subcommittee on Commercial and Administrative Law of the House
       Committee on Judiciary on the NEXTWAVE Settlement Legislation,
       December 6, 2001.
     * Speech by Chairman Powell at the Association for Local
       Telecommunications Services, November 30, 2001.  [speaker.gif]
     * Letter from Chairman Powell to U.S. Bankruptcy Court, California re
       Excite@Home high speed internet service, November 30, 2001.
     * Chairman Powell's Statement on Conclusion of Discussions on
       Nextwave Licenses, November 16, 2001.
     * Testimony of Thomas J. Sugrue, Hearing on Wireless E911, Before the
       Subcommittee on Communications of the Senate Committee on Commerce,
       Science and Transportation, October 16, 2001. [ Text | Acrobat ]
     * Statement of Chairman Powell Following Tour of New York Telephone
       Facilities and Discussion of Repair Efforts With Telephone
       Officials, September 20, 2001.
     * Statement of Commissioner Michael J. Copps on Complaints Received
       Regarding Howard Stern Broadcast on National Day of Prayer and
       Rememberance, September 20, 2001.
     * Testimony of Julius P. Knapp, Deputy Chief, Office of Engineering
       and Technology, before the Subcommittee on Communications of the
       Senate Committee on Commerce, Science and Transportation, July 31,
       2001. [ Text | Word97 | Acrobat ]
