   Intergovernmental Links

     * National Telecommunications and Information Administration (NTIA)
       Authority over government-use spectrum.
     * Universal Service Administrative Company (USAC)
       Authority over administration of the Universal Service fund.
     * Federal Trade Commission (FTC)
       Authority over truth-in-billing and Internet fraud.
     * Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers (ICANN)
       Authority over Internet addresses and domain names.
     * Federal Aviation Administration (FAA)
       Authority over airport communication towers.
     * North American Numbering Plan Administration (NANPA)
       Authority over assignment of area codes.
     * National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners (NARUC)
       Authority over energy transmission lines, towers and carriers.
     * International Telecommunication Union (ITU)
       Authority over international telecommunications treaties and
       interconnection of global networks.

